                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2000-04-22</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>Touching Base is a well-researched account of the sport of baseball during its formative years. This book explains how and why baseball became our favorite pastime and how the sport paralleled the life and challenges of  the American people during the first of the twentieth century. Great  comparisons between the myths and the realities of the game.</span>
                  
              
